## 2. Floating UI: Use Built-in Interaction Hooks

### Rule

**NEVER** reinvent hover/click/focus with manual `useState` + `setTimeout`.
**ALWAYS** use Floating UI's interaction hooks.

| Interaction | Hook | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Hover | `useHover(context, opts)` | Tooltip, HoverMenu |
| Click | `useClick(context, opts)` | Popover, Select |
| Dismiss | `useDismiss(context)` | All floating components |
| Role | `useRole(context, { role })` | All (a11y) |
| Focus | `useFocus(context)` | Tooltip (keyboard a11y) |

### Why

Manual hover state management bypasses Floating UI's `onOpenChange` flow.
This causes `useDismiss`, `whileElementsMounted`, and position calculation to be disconnected from the actual open state.

### Pattern (from Tooltip.tsx)

```tsx
const [open, setOpen] = useState(false)

const { refs, floatingStyles, context } = useFloating({
  open,
  onOpenChange: setOpen,     // Single source of truth
  whileElementsMounted: autoUpdate,
  middleware: [offset(8), flip(), shift()]
})

const hover = useHover(context, { delay: { open: 200, close: 0 } })
const dismiss = useDismiss(context)
const role = useRole(context, { role: 'tooltip' })

const { getReferenceProps, getFloatingProps } = useInteractions([hover, dismiss, role])
```

---

## 3. Floating UI: Use `strategy: 'fixed'` for Portalled Tooltips

### Rule

When a floating element renders in a `FloatingPortal` (at `<body>` level), use `strategy: 'fixed'`.

### Why

- `strategy: 'absolute'` can extend the document body → scrollbar appears → viewport resizes → `autoUpdate` fires → repositions → scrollbar disappears → **infinite feedback loop** (scroll glitch)
- `strategy: 'fixed'` positions relative to the viewport — **no document overflow possible**

```tsx
const { refs, floatingStyles, context } = useFloating({
  strategy: 'fixed',  // ✅ Prevents scroll glitches in portals
  // ...
})
```

---

## 4. React Rules of Hooks: No Conditional Returns Before Hooks

### Rule

**NEVER** place an early return before any hook call, even if the condition is a module-level constant.

```tsx
// ❌ BROKEN — hooks after conditional return
function Tooltip({ children }) {
  if (!canHover) return <>{children}</>  // early return!
  const [open, setOpen] = useState(false)  // hook AFTER conditional
}

// ✅ CORRECT — all hooks first, then early return
function Tooltip({ children }) {
  const [open, setOpen] = useState(false)  // hooks FIRST
  // ... all other hooks ...
  if (!canHover) return <>{children}</>    // early return AFTER hooks
}
```

---

## 5. Ref Composition with `useMergeRefs`

### Rule

When `cloneElement` replaces a child's ref, the original is lost. Always use `useMergeRefs` from `@floating-ui/react`.

```tsx
import { useMergeRefs } from '@floating-ui/react'

const childRef = isValidElement(children)
  ? (children as any).props?.ref ?? (children as any).ref ?? null
  : null
const mergedRef = useMergeRefs([refs.setReference, childRef])
```

This ensures:
- Floating UI gets its reference measurement (`refs.setReference`)
- The parent keeps its DOM handle (e.g., `forwardRef` callback)

---

## 6. Component-Level Tooltip Integration

### Rule

Tooltips should be integrated INTO components, not wrapped externally.

```tsx
// ❌ Repetitive external wrapping
<Tooltip title="Bold"><Button>B</Button></Tooltip>

// ✅ Built-in tooltip props
<Button tooltip="Bold" tooltipPlacement="bottom">B</Button>
<Avatar tooltip="Profile" tooltipPosition="bottom" />
```

### Components with Built-in Tooltip Support

| Component | Props | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `Button` | `tooltip`, `tooltipPlacement` | Wraps in `<Tooltip>` internally |
| `Avatar` | `tooltip`, `tooltipPosition` | Wraps in `<Tooltip>` internally |

### When to Use `<Tooltip>` Directly

- Non-Button/Avatar elements (e.g., `<div>`, `<span>`)
- Complex trigger elements
- Design system demos

---

## 7. Touch-Only Device Handling

### Rule

Tooltips are hover-based — disable on touch-only devices using CSS media query.

```tsx
const canHover =
  typeof window !== 'undefined'
    ? window.matchMedia('(hover: hover)').matches
    : true  // SSR fallback: assume hover
```

Place the check AFTER all hooks, as an early return:

```tsx
// All hooks called above...
if (!canHover) return <>{children}</>
```

---

## 8. Floating UI Component Architecture

All Floating UI components in this project follow the same pattern:

```
useFloating()           → positioning engine
useInteractions([...])  → event handlers
useMergeRefs([...])     → ref composition
getReferenceProps()     → props for trigger element
getFloatingProps()      → props for floating element
FloatingPortal          → renders at body level
```

### Existing Components

| Component | Interaction Hook | Strategy | Portal |
|---|---|---|---|
| `Tooltip` | `useHover` | `fixed` | Yes |
| `Popover` | `useClick` | `absolute` (default) | Yes |
| `Select` | `useClick` | `absolute` (default) | Yes |
| `SearchableSelect` | `useClick` | `absolute` (default) | Yes |
| `HoverMenu` | `useHover` | `absolute` (override to `fixed` in style) | Yes |
| `Dialog` | — (controlled) | — | Yes |

---

## 9. Naming Conventions

| Pattern | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Toolbar component | `EditorToolbar` (not `ToolbarDesktop`) | Feature-first naming |
| Select variant | `StyleSelect` (not `SelectHeadingBox`) | Purpose-first naming |
| Constants | `ICON_SIZE`, `PANEL_CLASS` | UPPER_SNAKE for module constants |
| Dynamic imports | `MediaInsertPanel` (not `InsertMultimediaForm`) | UI-facing name |
| Props | `tooltipPlacement` (not `tooltipPosition`) | Matches Floating UI `Placement` type |

---

## 10. Dark Theme Compliance

All overlay/floating components MUST include:

```tsx
// Border for visibility on dark backgrounds
className="border border-base-300"

// Elevated background (not base-100 which matches page bg in dark)
className="bg-base-200"

// Sufficient shadow
className="shadow-xl"  // or shadow-lg, not shadow-xs
```

### Components Affected

- `ContextMenu`, `Dialog`, `HoverMenu`, `Toast`, `Popover`, `Select`
